org.apache.ambari.server.state.kerberos

Class KerberosComponentDescriptor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.ambari.server.state.kerberos.AbstractKerberosDescriptor
      • org.apache.ambari.server.state.kerberos.AbstractKerberosDescriptorContainer
        • org.apache.ambari.server.state.kerberos.KerberosComponentDescriptor

  • public class KerberosComponentDescriptor
extends AbstractKerberosDescriptorContainer
    KerberosComponentDescriptor is an implementation of an AbstractKerberosDescriptorContainer that encapsulates the details about an Ambari component.

    A KerberosComponentDescriptor has the following properties:

    • identities (AbstractKerberosDescriptorContainer)
    • configurations (AbstractKerberosDescriptorContainer)

    The following (pseudo) JSON Schema will yield a valid KerberosComponentDescriptor 

       {
      "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-04/schema#",
      "title": "KerberosComponentDescriptor",
      "description": "Describes an Ambari component",
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "identities": {
          "description": "A list of Kerberos identity descriptors",
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "title": "KerberosIdentityDescriptor"
            "type": "KerberosIdentityDescriptor"
          }
        },
        "configurations": {
          "description": "A list of relevant configuration blocks",
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "title": "KerberosConfigurationDescriptor"
            "type": "KerberosConfigurationDescriptor"
          }
        }
      }
   }

    In this implementation, AbstractKerberosDescriptor.name will hold the KerberosComponentDescriptor#name value
